title.narrative: OUTPUT 1: ENABLING ENVIRONMENT HEALTH SYSTEM

description.narrative: Ghana health system has the necessary management tools to support effective service delivery at national and subnational levels, which contributes to Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, more children and women access and utilize quality health services

description.narrative: Ghana was the first country to receive COVID-19 vaccines from the COVAX facility; COVID-19 vaccine deployment initiated since 1st March 2021 with over 7 million COVID-19 vaccine doses successfully deployed; immunization cold chain systems strengthened at all levels with installation of eighteen (18) remote temperature monitoring devices in walk-in cold rooms across the country; a national policy on medical oxygen and costed strategy developed to contribute to effective management of childhood pneumonia and COVID-19 case management and a country assessment on lead contamination has been completed as part of the Global Protecting Every Child’s Potential (PCEP) partnership initiative.;;; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2022
